Former Gauteng Health MEC Qedani Mahlangu is appearing at the ongoing Life Esidimeni arbitration hearings in Parktown, Johannesburg today to account for her role in the saga. At least 143 mentally ill patients are known to have died following their transfer from  Life Esidimeni to unregistered NGOs. EARLIER: 10:00 am 10:05 AM 10:20 AM #LifeEsidimeni Mahlangu reads her statement says the loss of life was regrettable and painful. Her voice breaks as she says she sincerely apologizes for the tragedy.@ANN7tv @The_New_Age — Roving Reporter (@IamThandoD) January 22, 2018 Tweets by Nhlajules